  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are international laws and regulations against money laundering. Key organizations and frameworks include:\n\n1. Financial Action Task Force (FATF)\n- Sets global standards for combating money laundering\n- Develops recommendations for financial institutions and governments\n\n2. United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Provides framework for international cooperation\n- Requires countries to criminalize money laundering\n\n3. International Monetary Fund (IMF) Guidelines\n- Provides guidance on preventing financial crimes\n\n4. Basel Committee on Banking Supervision\n- Establishes international banking standards\n- Includes recommendations for preventing money laundering\n\n5. Individual Country Laws\n- Many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) legislation\n- Examples include the U.S. Bank Secrecy Act and European Union's AML Directives\n\n6. Know Your Customer (KYC) Regulations\n- Require financial institutions to verify customer identities\n- Help prevent illegal financial activities\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across international borders by promoting cooperation and setting common standards.",
